Window Report for ReactorControl

================================================================================

Object Type: Button
Object Name: btn_StartReactor
Link: Touch Pushbutton

Application Script:

  Comment: Fires once when the application starts. Initialises all tags.

  DIM bolInit AS Discrete;
  bolInit = False;

  IF NOT bolInit THEN
      LogMessage("Application started at: " + $DateTime);
      bolInit = True;
  ENDIF;

================================================================================

Object Type: Slider
Object Name: sld_TemperatureSetpoint

Data Change Script: Reactor1.Temperature

  Comment: Runs each time the Temperature tag value changes.

  DIM realTemp AS Real;
  DIM strAlert AS Message;

  realTemp = Reactor1.Temperature.Value;

  IF realTemp > 120.0 THEN
      strAlert = "CRITICAL high temperature: " + StringFromReal(realTemp, "%6.1f");
      LogMessage(strAlert);
      MessageBox(strAlert, 1);
      almAckTag("Reactor1.Temperature");
  ELSEIF realTemp > 80.0 THEN
      LogMessage("WARNING: Temperature rising - " + StringFromReal(realTemp, "%6.1f") + " " + Reactor1.Temperature.EngUnits);
  ENDIF;

================================================================================

Object Type: Text
Object Name: txt_StatusDisplay

Condition Script: $AccessLevel >= 2

  Comment: Shows maintenance panel only when operator has sufficient access.

  IF $AccessLevel >= 2 THEN
      Show("MaintenancePanel");
      LogMessage("Maintenance access granted for: " + $Operator);
  ELSE
      Hide("MaintenancePanel");
  ENDIF;

================================================================================

Object Type: Symbol
Object Name: sym_AlarmIndicator

Script on while Reactor1.AlarmActive == True

  Comment: Pulses the alarm indicator while the alarm condition persists.

  DIM bolFlash AS Discrete;

  bolFlash = NOT bolFlash;

  IF bolFlash THEN
      SetPropertyD("sym_AlarmIndicator", "Visible", True);
  ELSE
      SetPropertyD("sym_AlarmIndicator", "Visible", False);
  ENDIF;

================================================================================

Object Type: Trend
Object Name: trn_ReactorTrend

  Comment: Historical trend for reactor temperature and setpoint.

  #Trend1.DisplayMode = 0;
  #Trend1.ChartLength = 3600;
  #Trend1.MinRange    = 0.0;
  #Trend1.MaxRange    = 200.0;
  HTUpdateToCurrentTime("Trend1");

